According to <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/89773100@N02/8287722110/">this</a> article in Freeman's in 1878, (which will tell you everything you ever wanted to know about street watering, and more besides) the cost of street watering in London was a staggering £135,000 per annum.
<blockquote><i>This is the sum expended in the distribution of the water by horses and carts</i></blockquote>

It also mentions &quot;the laborious hydrant and hose system of watering&quot;
